      "description": "One rule conflates three distinct facets — colorway/variant spec (0001), layered construction with fixed 70% transparency (0002), and flexible usage guidance (0003) — that differ in hardness/polarity. The construction clause ('always preserve') is a true hard must, but the usage clause ('alone, or overlaid...to support...') is permissive/optional, not a hard must. Should be split into at least two rules: one for construction (hard/must) and one for usage/application (soft, should/may).",
